info.x_cadence_note: Cadence based on variable 'Epoch_ChanC' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/psp/isois/epilo/l2/ic/2018/psp_isois-epilo_l2-ic_20180928_v21.cdf. This most common cadence occurred for 48.0000% of the 12 timesteps. Cadence = 1199999955000 [ns] = PT19M59.999955S.

parameters.name: He3_CountRate_ChanC_avg
parameters.description: ---> He3 count rate channel C (Ions1). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function spdf_3d_to_2d_avg_over_col (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['He3_CountRate_ChanC']. Note that not all COMPONENTS are time series and so their values are not available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
